  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Caritas Harare Bridging Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims at strengthening and sustaining the results achieved under the three year Sanitation for Success project implemented in Murehwa District.  The project will focus on waste management, recycling which holds a direct link to the second result area of a cleaner, safer more functional environment. It is anticipated that the waste management and recycling activities proposed will lead to income generation for the young people involved and that they will improve the environment through waste collection and clean energy generation. The project will contribute to the Dialogue and progress that is being called for by Pope Francis in the Encyclical Laudato Si on Care for the Common Home. Caritas will work with 10 Parishes in the outer City and South Western City and Eastern Deaneries of the Archdiocese of Harare to implement the Laudato Si.</narrative>
  </description>
